---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';

const frontmatter = {
  title: 'How to build a resilient growth strategy in 2026',
  description: 'A practical framework for choosing priorities in a shifting market.',
  category: 'Strategy',
  tags: ['growth', 'planning'],
  readingTime: '6 min read',
};
---

<BaseLayout title={frontmatter.title} description={frontmatter.description} type="article">
  <Navbar />
  <main>
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container prose">
        <p class="eyebrow">{frontmatter.category}</p>
        <h1>{frontmatter.title}</h1>
        <div class="blog-meta">
          <span class="pill">{frontmatter.readingTime}</span>
          {frontmatter.tags.map((tag) => <span class="pill">#{tag}</span>)}
        </div>
        <p>Growth is rarely about doing more. It is often about making a few deliberate decisions with confidence and consistency.</p>
        <h2>Start with the signal</h2>
        <p>Look for patterns in customer feedback, delivery data, and team capacity before you adjust your plan. The best strategies are grounded in what the business is already experiencing.</p>
        <h2>Choose a small number of priorities</h2>
        <p>When a team tries to tackle too much at once, momentum weakens. Focus on the areas where a meaningful improvement can compound over time.</p>
        <h2>Keep the plan visible</h2>
        <p>Teams perform better when strategy is clear, shared, and easy to revisit. A simple operating rhythm helps people stay aligned without constant intervention.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
